cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper is about improving contextualized word embeddings, which is a topic within natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also introduces a new architecture based on a pretrained BERT model, which involves deep neural networks and could fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper evaluates the performance of the proposed method on downstream tasks, which could also relate to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) if the tasks involve image or video processing.
